        <num>860-D</num>
        <heading>Extension of mass layoff period</heading>
        <content>
          <p>  ยง 860-d. Extension of mass layoff period. A mass layoff of more than\nsix months which, at its outset, was announced to be a mass layoff of\nsix months or less shall be treated as an employment loss under this\narticle unless:\n  1. the extension beyond six months is caused by business circumstances\n(including unforeseeable changes in price or cost) not reasonably\nforeseeable at the time of the initial mass layoff; and\n  2. notice is given at the time it becomes reasonably foreseeable that\nthe extension beyond six months will be required.\n</p>
        </content>
      </section>
